content.description: Great little route that is fun, a touch airy, and well protected, great for a first lead. The crux is probably the very last move stepping onto a small ledge and with no hands standing up to clip the anchor. If it feels off balance, just grab the chains.
content.protection: 3 quickdraws, plus chains at the top.
content.location: The first east-facing route at Headlight, following flakes just off the trail. (Second route at Headlight.)

content.description: Cruiser moves until the last bit with something more thought-provoking before the chains.
content.location: Shared start with Carnage, to the right of Nocturnal Remission

content.description: Pull off the ground and climb through a short but steep overhanging bulge.  After pulling the bulge, a short vertical face leads to chains.
content.location: This route is on the Headlight Point side of the gully that divides Headlight Point from Eastern Block. Head up the rocky gully until near the large wedged chockstone called the  "Block of Doom".  When looking up toward the "Block of Doom", Silent Service will be on the climber's left.

climbs.name: Railway
climbs.fa: Leland Windham, Vincent Bailey, David Wolfe

content.description:
P1 Begin under the Block of Doom and traverse left on a rail above and past Silent Service and Eating Dust anchors. 11 bolts

P2 Go up for two bolts, then split off left and traverse. Route joins 5.8 Insomniac with easier climbing on the soft arete. Reach an anchor with single chain links. Then pass one bolt and head up the slab to the summit where the Insomniac anchor is located. 7 bolts
content.location: In the Block of Doom Gully, line traverses on the left wall.

climbs.name: Raceway
climbs.fa: Leland Windham, Vincent Bailey, David Smith

content.description:
Climb Railway, Eating Rocks or Eating Dust.

Move left with tricky moves onto a slab. Run out between 3rd and 4th bolts, a fall here would be gnarly. Bring gear for the crack. There is a huge loose block under the Bicycle of Bellingham anchor that could knock someone unconscious down below. Â Continue straight up to Insomniac anchor.
content.location: Pitch above Eating Rocks and Eating Dust.

content.description: Consistent climbing up a blocky looking face. Good holds a plenty.
content.location: In a slight depression in the cliff. A left leaning short ramp is the start and then you pull straight up the cliff.

content.description: Climb up through easy terrain to anchors just out of view to the left of a large jut of rock you see from the ground.
content.location: Currently the second sport route you come to as you approach Headlight point from the parking lot. Just to the left of Swerve.

content.description: Fun, short romp up good holds on solid rock
content.location: One of the first routes encountered when approaching Interstate Park.  On the first face, before the alcove for Nocturnal Remission

content.description: Above and left of Eating Rocks. Follow the left facing dihedral up and right. Don't head for the chains on the right face, but instead stay left and go over the angled slabby ledges. You can't see all the bolts from below, but you'll find them as you move up. The anchor chains are just over the top of the slab, and you'll lower into the gap below the "block of doom".
'Start on Midnight Scrambler, then exit right after the 2nd bolt to finish at the Light-Headed Again anchors' (Kurt Hicks, Snoqualmie Rock guide)

climbs.name: Hidden Block
climbs.fa: Leland Windham, David Wolfe, Jim Mallory & Brandon and Heather Kern (2004)

content.description: Steep crimpy climbing on a short blank wall.
content.location: In the Block of Doom gully, 40 feet back from and above the Block of Doom. Shaded most of the day. You can climb Tunnel of Love and scramble over, or access it from the trail above Squishy Bell.

content.description: the left of two easy routes on the left side of the gulley below the block of doom.
right of eating rocks. left side of the gulley below the block of doom
Shared start with Swarm.  Step right and pull through an overhanging section on good holds.  Meet back up with Swarm toward the top.
content.location: Shared start with Swarm, stepping right.

content.description: Find a crack to the left that crosses Insomniac as it curves back to the right as a ramp. Head right on another crack to a roof with a bolt. Crux is the roof area.
content.location: Start at the bolted stance beneath Insomniac.

climbs.name: As the Apocalypse Revs Up
climbs.fa: Leland Windham, Jack Hemstreet, Lauri jae Sweetland, May 2020

content.description: Short and sweet. Scramble start, up through some crimps and cool undercling, over a bulge with good movement, and straight up to the anchor.
content.location: Left down the trail from Swerve. The first route encountered. In between this and the Swerve start is some dirty bushes and a few trees on the corner of the crag.
